p: The gas chromatography-mass spectrometry (GC-MS) analysis of MCEO using a nonpolar column revealed the presence of 41 chemical components with a composition of 98% ( Table 1). The major compounds of MCEO were identified as linalool 19.1%, geranial 15.7%, citronellal 14.1%, neral 13.5%, and sabinene 12.4%. The MCEO was dominated by oxygenated monoterpenoids (77.8%), followed by monoterpene hydrocarbons (17.3%), sesquiterpene hydrocarbons (0.8%), oxygenated sesquiterpenes (0.3%), and others (1.8%).
